9438248, 0.008935678750276566, 0.07311995327472687, -0.005856080912053585, -0.025409454479813576, 0.007388334721326828, -0.05199458822607994, -0.02653084695339203, -0.03135216236114502, 0.057260867208242416, 0.06789185851812363, 0.04244222491979599, -0.009965869598090649, -0.001485682325437665, 0.0756877139210701, 0.009240463376045227, 0.04327435418963432, -0.018551528453826904, -0.046329911798238754, 0.013462088070809841], "metadata": {"text": "CHADALAWADA RAMANAMMAENGINEERING COLLEGE   \n(AUTONOMOUS)   \nApproved by AICTE, Accredited by NAAC and Permanently Affiliated to JNTUA, Anantapuramu  \nChadalawadaNagar, Renigunta Road, Tirupati \u2013 517 506  \nDEPARTMENT OF COMPUTER SCIENCE AND ENGINEERING   \n AcademicYear  \nLevel  \nYear&Semester  \nCourse  \nCourse code  : 2025 -26  \n: UG -B.Tech  \n: IV Year - II Semester  \n: Project  \n: 20 CA 02801  \n  \n              Name of the Title  : Privacy -Preserving keyword search wi th Access Control in Data Outsourcing .  \nABSTRACT   \nThis work proposes a privacy -preserving keyword search system  that allows users to search encrypted data \nstored in the cloud while enforcing access control . Unlike traditional searchable encryption based on expensive \npublic -key operations, the method uses secret sharing , which is computationally lightweight.  \nEach data item is encrypted using a (k, n) threshold secret sharing sc heme . Data owners control who can access \nand search their data. Secure computations are performed collaboratively by the owner, a player, and at least k out \nof n cloud servers. The system ensures that even if up to k\u20131 servers behave honestly -but-curiously , they cannot \nlearn anything about the data or keywords.  \nThe work also presents a more efficient version using (n, n) additive secret sharing , analyzes the security of all \nphases (data distribution, query generation, search), and compares computational an d communication \nperformance. A Python -based implementation demonstrates the efficiency gains compared to existing methods.  \n  \nKeywords:  \n   Privacy -Preserving Search, Encrypted Data, Keyword Search, Access Control, Cloud computing  \nBatch: \u2013 11  \nBatch mem bers:  \n1. V. SAI CHARAN                                      \u2013 22P11A05B4  \n2. M.TEJASWI NI                                      \u2013 22P11A0579  \n3. P. BALAJI              \u2013 22P11A0586  \n4. N. PRASANNA KUMAR    \u2013 23P15A0508   \n  \n                    Project guide                                                             Head of the department  \n                    Mrs.M.Bhanu Priya                                                Dr.D.Shobha Rani ,Ph.D .  \n               Assistant Professor                                                                    Professor  \n  \n", "source": "abstract_11.pdf", "chunk_id": 0}}, {"vector": [-0.04766739904880524, 0.006762784440070391, -0.05205869674682617, -0.00874264258891344, -0.03631206601858139, -0.11965079605579376, 0.08641156554222107, 0.04565197229385376, -0.12545228004455566, 0.01704402267932892, 0.0045988187193870544, -0.11973688006401062, 0.05933696776628494, -0.04494502395391464, -0.019690657034516335, 0.1198168694972992, -0.021247006952762604, -0.05027181655168533, -0.005624981597065926, -0.0678788423538208, -0.05587254837155342, -0.013472890481352806, -0.05463966727256775, -0.0739249661564827, 0.043906956911087036, 0.0938788652420044, -0.001769026042893529, -0.01682928018271923, 0.0156345684081316, -0.07857649773359299, -0.0502474419772625, -0.025713488459587097, -0.014150856994092464, 0.11546268314123154, -0.004234530497342348, 0.08778452128171921, -0.03155946731567383, -0.015709534287452698, -0.01126136351376772, -0.03890395909547806, -0.07360558956861496, -0.020499667152762413, -0.020611966028809547, -0.06110070273280144, 0.018810855224728584, -0.09343183040618896, -0.08647515624761581, -0.031016139313578606, 0.022385207936167717, -0.017518728971481323, -0.1342482715845108, -0.088835433