te real-time game outcome evaluation.\nBudget Tracker Web Application Dec 2025 \u2013 Jan 2026\nHTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+), LocalStorage, Frontend Development Live Demo\n\u2022Engineered a responsive financial tracking application using JavaScript ES6, implementing modular architecture,\nclasses, and dynamic DOM manipulation.\n\u2022Integrated LocalStorage API for persistent client-side data management, enabling secure storage and retrieval of\nincome, expense, and balance records.\n\u2022Developed real-time balance calculation and transaction management system with validation logic, ensuring data\nintegrity and improved user experience.\nPrivacy-Preserving Keyword Search with Access Control Dec 2025 \u2013 Present\nHTML, CSS, Java Script, Cloud Security, Encryption, MySQL\n\u2022Designed and developed a secure cloud-based system enabling keyword search over encrypted data without exposing\nsensitive information.\n\u2022Implemented role-based access control and threshold-based secret sharing to ensure authorized data access.\n\u2022Improved search efficiency by optimizing secure query execution and reducing computational overhead.\nInternship Experience\nJava Full Stack Developer Intern \u2013 TAP Academy Nov 2025 \u2013 Present\nJava, MySQL, HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, JDBC Bengaluru, India\n\u2022Developing full-stack applications using Java for backend processing and MySQL for relational database manage-\nment, implementing efficient data storage, retrieval, and transaction handling.\n\u2022Designed and integrated dynamic user interfaces using HTML5, CSS3, and JavaScript with optimized DOM ma-\nnipulation and client-side validation to enhance user experience and application performance.\n\u2022Implemented JDBC-based database connectivity to perform CRUD operations, applied Object-Oriented Program-\nming (OOP), modular architecture, and structured exception handling to ensure scalable, maintainable, and robust\nsoftware solutions.\n1\nFrontend Developer Intern \u2013 CodTech IT Solutions May 2025 \u2013 Jul 2025\nReact.js, REST APIs, AI Remote\n\u2022Built responsive and reusable UI components using React functional components and hooks.\n\u2022Integrated backend APIs and implemented client-side routing.\n\u2022Used Git for version control and debugging tools to enhance application stability.\nLeadership & Achievements\n\u2022Served as CSE Department Association Coordinator, leading technical events and student teams.\n\u2022Actively participated in coding workshops and technical seminars.\nEducation\nChadalawada Ramanamma Engineering College Aug 2023 \u2013 Jul 2026\nB.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering(CGPA: 8.37)Andhra Pradesh\nGuntur Engineering College Oct 2020 \u2013 Jun 2023\nDiploma in Civil Engineering(CGPA: 8.51)Andhra Pradesh\n2\n", "source": "Prasannakumar_Tap_Resume.pdf", "chunk_id": 1}}, {"vector": [-0.09738797694444656, 0.0336918868124485, -0.02998044341802597, -0.0200562234967947, -0.02554306946694851, 0.010772289708256721, 0.07334606349468231, -0.07936226576566696, 0.020956920459866524, 0.037259723991155624, 0.04046223685145378, 0.02423417754471302, 0.13572601974010468, -0.10826165229082108, 0.027251796796917915, -0.022493327036499977, 0.0012610523262992501, -0.0043116724118590355, -0.09708105772733688, -0.0963558629155159, -0.016350578516721725, -0.06299103051424026, -0.007452244870364666, -0.004498539958149195, -0.03736942261457443, 0.03163064643740654, 0.018889956176280975, -0.08865124732255936, -0.03588011860847473, -0.03808462992310524, 0.033512867987155914, -0.03335605561733246, 0.04770306870341301, 0.16272112727165222, -0.027100617066025734, -0.05306413397192955, -0.08862991631031036, -0.00034026516368612647, -0.016936445608735085, -0.028698574751615524, -0.12126634269952774, -0.06874203681945801, -0.12258809804916382, -0.017833227291703224, -0.02789953537285328, 0.057867079973220825, -0.010708105750381947, 0.011590083129703999, 0.011502237990498543, -0.005491503048688173, -0.06538958102464676,